rComments: Easy class, but the prof is unprofessional. Posted our exam 30 minutes late, gave us class during reading week, made a review session during reading week and showed up 30 minutes late to both of our review sessions. Was supposed to have 4.5 hours of class, but we just had one prerecorded PowerPoint instead which didn't help w comprehension, avoid!

Monsieur Jacob est un prof assez particulier. Nous avons été notés sur un examen de mi-session, notre participation (il accordait 100% à tlm) et un travail final. La mi-session a été corrigée assez sévèrement. Il avait beaucoup de lectures pour l'examen. En général un bon prof.
One of the rare professors that shows he really loves what he does. Definitely recommend him to anyone! class material is also very fair and he is super understanding to personal circumstances

Of all classes to have to take on a Friday night at 6pm, I never thought I would enjoy it as much as I have with Rafael. He genuinely cares about his students, provides us with practice exams prior to each test, and never kept us for the entire lecture. Always energized with a smile on his face, he made stats much better than I thought it could be!
Great professor! Very enthusiastic and creates a great class environment. Highly suggest him!

This review is for Poli 331 at Concordia University Montreal. Great professor who gives clear lectures on what is to be expected during assessments. Did not do a single reading, showed up each class and listened to what he emphasized on making note. Solid grader and gives fair exams/papers. Would highly recommend. Received A+, no failures.

His lectures are interesting and very informative. If you do your readings and attend the lectures, you will succeed in this class. Participation is encouraged but not mandatory. The best part is that all readings are posted online and the final exam was early, which took the load off during the week of final exams.
Great teacher, has high standards but gives you every tool necessary to reach those high standards. Very funny.

Extremely helpfull. He often goes out of his way to assist students and make sure everyone is on board before moving forward. Also, creates a laidback atmosphere in class. This was great for this particular course.
Lots of readings (not always super-interesting) made up by the prof being really into it, in his element.
Good prof. Had him for stats. Funny and engaging.

C'est un excellent prof. Il est dynamique et drôle. Les cours sont relativement faciles à suivre. La correction des travaux est juste et vrai. Ils ne sont pas complexes, mais ils sont impossibles à faire la veille !! Les textes sont nombreux et nécessaires à la compréhension du contenu vu en classe. Il pose toujours des questions !!

He's personable and has high standards  (but is fair). Actually, the negative reviewer below inadvertently makes  that point.  ''He really count the quality of the language.'' Yeah, if you can't structure a proper sentence, maybe you shouldn't expect to do great in a 3rd-year university course in *communications*!  Great prof, interesting class.
He really count the quality of the language. His explanations are never clear even if you go see him. Honestly I did not learn anything in his class.

A very fair and interesting prof. He gave us 3 or 4 scholarly articles per week to read and the classes were entirely based off of them (Political Communications). No midterm, no exam, just three 5-6p. papers. Read or at least skim the texts, go to class and have a good time.
